AI Lesson Builder

Goal:
User selects source materials or describes a topic in extra instructions, and AI turns it into a clear theoretical internal knowledge article / lesson. If materials are selected, AI combines them into one coherent learning flow.

Key principle:
The lesson should not be a simple summary and should not become a generic course template. It should merge the selected materials structurally, explain concepts clearly where the source lacks context, remove duplication, preserve source-specific caveats, avoid unsupported filler, and produce useful Markdown for digital marketing agency employees.

Phase 1 - Product shape and UX
[x] Define lesson creation flow:
    [x] Select source materials from library, optional.
    [x] Add extra user instructions.
    [x] Allow prompt-only lesson generation when no materials are selected.
    [x] Add optional lesson settings: depth, tone, desired format.
    [x] Preview selected material titles before generation.
    [x] Start lesson generation and show progress/status.
[x] Decide lesson output structure:
    [x] Title.
    [x] Direct main content sections.
    [x] Prerequisites only if truly necessary.
    [x] Examples and analogies only when they clarify source material.
    [x] Key terms / definitions only if useful and not already explained inline.
    [x] Summary.
[x] Define MVP limits:
    [x] Maximum number of selected materials: 8.
    [x] Maximum combined extracted text size: 80,000 characters.
    [x] Supported material types for first version: library material title, description, text content, links, YouTube URLs, and attachment metadata. File text extraction can be added later.

Phase 2 - Data model
[x] Add lesson entity:
    [x] id, title, description, status.
    [x] selected material ids through lesson_materials.
    [x] user instructions.
    [x] generated lesson content.
    [x] generation metadata: model, prompt version, token usage, provider response id, createdBy, createdAt, updatedAt.
[x] Add lesson draft/generation states:
    [x] draft.
    [x] generating.
    [x] ready.
    [x] failed.
[x] Decide how to store generated content:
    [x] Markdown for MVP.
    [x] Structured JSON blocks later if editing/reordering sections is needed.

Phase 3 - Material preparation
[x] Build material aggregation step:
    [x] Load selected materials.
    [x] Normalize titles, descriptions, links, YouTube URLs, attachment metadata, and text content.
    [x] Keep source references so the generated lesson can cite where ideas came from.
[x] Add preprocessing:
    [x] Trim irrelevant whitespace and duplicate URLs.
    [x] Chunk large materials if needed later; for MVP, block generation above the size limit.
    [x] Detect duplicate titles and repeated URLs.
    [x] Extract candidate terms, examples, and caveats/warnings with basic text signals.
[x] Add validation:
    [x] No selected materials allowed if extra instructions describe the lesson topic.
    [x] Block generation when both selected materials and instructions are empty.
    [x] Materials too large.
    [x] Empty material content.

Phase 4 - AI lesson generation prompt
[x] Design the main prompt:
    [x] Explain that AI must synthesize materials, not just summarize them.
    [x] Require a coherent lesson flow with smooth transitions.
    [x] Require useful theoretical explanation without formal course scaffolding.
    [x] Require explicit handling of contradictions, missing context, and uncertainty.
    [x] Respect user instructions, depth, tone, and desired format.
    [x] Prevent generic filler like unsupported "why this matters" sections.
    [x] Ask AI to add concise background explanations for underexplained concepts when needed.
[x] Create a strict output format:
    [x] Free Markdown for MVP.
    [x] Do not require Short Description, Learning Objectives, or Lesson Outline.
    [x] Optional JSON schema later for editable blocks.
[x] Add prompt versioning:
    [x] Store prompt version on each generated lesson.
    [x] Keep prompts in a dedicated file/module.
    [x] Current prompt version: theoretical-lesson-v2.

Phase 5 - Backend API
[x] Add temporary endpoint/action to build and inspect the lesson prompt before real generation.
[x] Add endpoint/action to create lesson generation request.
[ ] Add endpoint/action to fetch lesson by id as a separate route.
[x] Add endpoint/action to list generated lessons.
[x] Add error handling for failed generation.
[x] Add basic logging for selected materials, prompt version, token usage, and failures.
[x] Save generated Markdown to lessons.content_markdown.
[x] Save generation metadata: provider, model, prompt version, response id, usage, prepared materials.
[x] Fix lesson_materials.material_id type to match materials.id UUID.
[x] Support prompt-only lesson generation without lesson_materials rows.

